      "content": "Even if the drops are water-based, introducing them into an infected eye can potentially push bacteria deeper into the eye tissue. While lubricating drops are designed to be sterile, using them excessively can lead to an imbalance of the natural eye flora. It's still not recommended to use \"heavily\" or excessively, but direct, short-term use (3-4 times a day) is usually recommended to help soothe and flush out debris.",
